President Biden addressed the nation in a briefing from the South Court Auditorium, providing updates on the COVID-19 pandemic. He emphasized the rising cases of the Omicron variant and urged people to protect themselves by getting vaccinated, boosted, and wearing masks in public. The President highlighted that those who are fully vaccinated and boosted are highly protected against severe illness, but the unvaccinated are at risk. He encouraged parents to get their children vaccinated and stated that schools should remain open, as they have the necessary funding and resources to keep students safe. President Biden also discussed the availability of booster shots, testing options, and the new Pfizer pill that reduces the risk of hospitalization and death. He directed his team to double the order of the Pfizer pill to 20 million treatment courses. The President concluded by urging people to use the available tools and medications to protect themselves and others, expressing hope for the future and the ability to overcome the pandemic together.